        <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>*pazdaka-</w></mentioned>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                                ><lang/><w>pazd</w><gloss><q>дым</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*pazd-
                        (pzt-)</w><gloss><q>дым</q></gloss></mentioned>. Как <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>дым</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"
                                ><lang/><w>*dhūm-</w></mentioned>) связано с <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>дуть</w></mentioned>, так %ipazd-%i происходит от
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pazd-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"
                        ><lang/><w>pezd-</w><gloss><q>дуть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"><w/><gloss><q>испускать вонь, дым</q></gloss></mentioned>, и
                пр. (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sl"><lang/><w>pezdêti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>pēdo</w></mentioned> и пр.). Поэтому относится сюда
                же <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                        ><lang/><w>nāy-pazd</w><gloss><q>флейтист</q></gloss></mentioned>
                                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._BBB"
                        /><biblScope>112</biblScope></bibl>), буквально „дующий (%ipazd-%i) в флейту
                        (nāy)“.<note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note> Стоит отметить, что в ряде языков
                эта же основа выступает в названии (вредных) насекомых: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                                ><lang/><w>pazdak</w><gloss><q>хлебный клещ</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>pazdu-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="uk"><lang/><w>бздюх</w><gloss><q>клоп</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                        ><lang/><w>pēdis</w><gloss><q>вошь</q></gloss></mentioned>. По форме и
                значению ос. %ifæzdæg%i смыкается с согдийским и ягнобским.%n<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Benveniste._TSP"/><biblScope>197</biblScope></bibl>. —
                                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>120</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                        ><lang/><w>*pazdaka-</w></mentioned>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                                ><lang/><w>pazd</w><gloss><q>smoke</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*pazd-
                                (pzt-)</w><gloss><q>smoke</q></gloss></mentioned>. The same way as
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><lang/><w>дым</w><gloss><q>smoke</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*dhūm-</w></mentioned>) is related to <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>дуть</w><gloss><q>blow</q></gloss></mentioned>, the
                word %ipazd-%i originates from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                        ><lang/><w>*pazd-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"
                                ><lang/><w>pezd-</w><gloss><q>blow</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"><w/><gloss><q>give off a stench,
                        smoke</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc. (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sl"
                                ><lang/><w>pezdêti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                                ><lang/><w>pēdo</w></mentioned> etc.). That is why <mentioned
                        xml:lang="pal"
                        ><lang/><w>nāy-pazd</w><gloss><q>flutist</q></gloss></mentioned> is related
                to it as well (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._BBB"
                        /><biblScope>112</biblScope></bibl>), literally ‘blowing (%ipazd-%i) in a
                flute (%ināy%i)’.<note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note> It should be noted that in a
                number of languages the same basis appears in the name of (destructive) insects:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pazdak</w><gloss><q>food
                        mite</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                        ><lang/><w>pazdu-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uk"
                                ><lang/><w>бздюх</w><gloss><q>bedbug</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                        ><lang/><w>pēdis</w><gloss><q>louse</q></gloss></mentioned>. In its form
                and its meaning Ossetic %ifæzdæg%i merges with Sogdian and Yaghnobi.%n<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Benveniste._TSP"/><biblScope>197</biblScope></bibl>. —
                                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>120</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
